The paper discusses the use of knowledge organization systems (KOS) for subject access to information systems, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The focus is on mapping between vocabularies, which involves both natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of automated mapping approaches, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the specific domain of agriculture is mentioned, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of digital libraries (cs.DL).
